essionInfo structure.\n1966: \n1967: **Step 5: Verify TestCase-ST-002 implementation**\n1968: \n1969: Ensure that store tests verify correct TTL (24h default) is set on keys.\n1970: \n1971: **Step 6: Verify TestCase-PD-001 implementation**\n1972: \n1973: Ensure that execution tests cover Python code execution with correct stdout and exitCode.\n1974: \n1975: **Step 7: Verify TestCase-PD-002 implementation**\n1976: \n1977: Ensure that execution tests cover error handling with stderr containing SyntaxError for invalid code.\n1978: \n1979: ---\n1980: \n1981: ### Task 17: Final verification\n1982: \n1983: **Step 1: Run all tests together**\n1984: \n1985: ```bash\n1986: go test -v ./pkg/router/... ./pkg/store/... ./pkg/picod/...\n1987: ```\n1988: \n1989: **Step 2: Check for race conditions**\n1990: \n1991: ```bash\n1992: go test -race ./pkg/router/... ./pkg/store/... ./pkg/picod/...\n1993: ```\n1994: \n1995: **Step 3: Run linter**\n1996: \n1997: ```bash\n1998: golangci-lint run ./pkg/router/... ./pkg/store/... ./pkg/picod/...\n1999: ```\n2000: \n2001: **Step 4: Verify all acceptance criteria**\n2002: \n2003: - [x] All core components have corresponding *_test.go files\n2004: - [x] Test coverage >80%\n2005: - [x] All tests can run successfully\n2006: - [x] Tests follow testify/assert pattern\n2007: - [x] Test cases cover normal flow, edge cases, and error scenarios\n2008: - [x] Tests follow test_spec.md requirements\n2009: \n2010: ---\n2011: \n2012: ## Helper Functions for Tests\n2013: \n2014: ```go\n2015: // Helper to convert struct to JSON bytes\n2016: func toJSON(v interface{}) []byte {\n2017:     data, err := json.Marshal(v)\n2018:     if err != nil {\n2019:         panic(err)\n2020:     }\n2021:     return data\n2022: }\n2023: \n2024: // Mock store for testing\n2025: type mockStore struct{}\n2026: \n2027: func (m *mockStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error { return nil }\n2028: func (m *mockStore) GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) { return nil, nil }\n2029: func (m *mockStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error { return nil }\n2030: func (m *mockStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error { return nil }\n2031: func (m *mockStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error { return nil }\n2032: func (m *mockStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) { return nil, nil }\n2033: func (m *mockStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) { return nil, nil }\n2034: func (m *mockStore) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error { return nil }\n2035: func (m *mockStore) Close() error { return nil }\n2036: ```\n2037: \n2038: ---\n2039: \n2040: ## Summary\n2041: \n2042: This implementation plan breaks down AR-039 into 17 atomic, independently verifiable tasks:\n2043: \n2044: **Phase 1: pkg/router Module Tests** (Tasks 1-5)\n2045: - Task 1: Create errors_test.go\n2046: - Task 2: Create proxy_test.go\n2047: - Task 3: Create resource_helpers_test.go\n2048: - Task 4: Create server_test.go\n2049: - Task 5: Create utils_test.go\n2050: \n2051: **Phase 2: pkg/store Module Tests** (Tasks 6-7)\n2052: - Task 6: Create store_test.go\n2053: - Task 7: Create singleton_test.go\n2054: \n2055: **Phase 3: pkg/picod Module Tests** (Tasks 8-14)\n2056: - Task 8: Create config_test.go\n2057: - Task 9: Create constants_test.go\n2058: - Task 10: Create errors_test.go\n2059: - Task 11: Create execute_test.go\n2060: - Task 12: Create files_test.go\n2061: - Task 13: Create handlers_test.go\n2062: - Task 14: Create informer_test.go\n2063: \n2064: **Phase 4: Integration and Verification** (Tasks 15-17)\n2065: - Task 15: Run all tests and verify coverage\n2066: - Task 16: Verify test_spec.md compliance\n2067: - Task 17: Final verification\n2068: \n2069: